import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Species')
    plt.ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'], data['Beak_Length__mm_'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Beak Length (mm)')
    plt.title('How does beak length vary with respect to beak depth?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Species').mean()
    plt.bar(data.index, data['Flipper_Length__mm_'])
    plt.title('What is the average flipper length for each species?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['Flipper_Length__mm_'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Beak_Depth__mm_'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Dream'], alpha=0.5, label='Dream')
    ax.hist(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Torgersen'], alpha=0.5, label='Torgersen')
    ax.hist(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Biscoe'], alpha=0.5, label='Biscoe')
    ax.axvline(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Dream'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Dream Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Dream'].mean()))
    ax.axvline(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Torgersen'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Torgersen Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Torgersen'].mean()))
    ax.axvline(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Biscoe'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Biscoe Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['Beak_Depth__mm_'][data['Island'] == 'Biscoe'].mean()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Beak Depth (mm)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Sex'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']['Body_Mass__g_'], data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']['Body_Mass__g_']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['MALE', 'FEMALE'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass for male and female penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['MALE Median: {:.2f}'.format(data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']['Body_Mass__g_'].median()), 'FEMALE Median: {:.2f}'.format(data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']['Body_Mass__g_'].median())])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
